To build with a particular interface into alquimia, run make as:

make PFLOTRAN_DIR=/path/to/pflotran all
make CRUNCH_DIR=/path/to/crunch all
make PFLOTRAN_DIR=/path/to/pflotran CRUNCH_DIR=/path/to/crunch all

To build with debug symbols:

make DEBUG=1 PFLOTRAN_DIR=${HOME}/projects/alquimia/pflotran-dev all

You should see compiler lines that look like:

$ make DEBUG=1 PFLOTRAN_DIR=${HOME}/projects/alquimia/pflotran-dev all
g++ -DHAVE_PFLOTRAN -g -I.   -c -o alquimia_interface_factory.o alquimia_interface_factory.cc
g++ -DHAVE_PFLOTRAN -g -I.   -c -o pflotran_alquimia_interface.o pflotran_alquimia_interface.cc
...
...


Test the buildsystem by running "make clobber" to remove all object
files, libraries and executables and start from scratch with make all.